  <main>
    <p class="lead">
      The Flight Delay Service is available to eligible customers who add this service during booking.
    </p>

    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The service monitors the status of your booked flight in real time.</li>
      <li>If your flight's departure is delayed beyond the minimum qualifying period stated in your booking confirmation, you may become eligible for the associated benefit.</li>
      <li>Flight status is sourced from recognized flight data providers.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Eligibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The service applies only to the flight itinerary linked to the booking reference provided at purchase.</li>
      <li>Valid for the specific journey for which it was purchased.</li>
      <li>Customers must provide accurate booking and contact details.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Service Benefit</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Where a qualifying delay occurs, the applicable benefit is processed in line with the parameters communicated at the time of purchase.</li>
      <li>Benefit eligibility is determined using actual recorded flight data.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Exclusions</h2>
    <p class="body-text">The service does not apply where:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Incorrect booking details have been provided.</li>
      <li>The customer voluntarily changes, cancels, or does not board the flight.</li>
      <li>The delay cannot be verified through official flight records.</li>
      <li>Duplicate bookings have been made for the same traveler and journey.</li>
    </ul>

